                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/225D.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">O’Brien</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d75fn1">Repeated to France, Germany, Great Britain, The
                        Netherlands, Portugal, and China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-06-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Adee directs Mr. O’Brien to inform the minister for foreign affairs that the
                    President has appointed Hon. Thomas Burke, Dr. Hamilton Wright, and Dr. Charles
                    D. Tenney American commissioners, joint international commission, to investigate
                    opium in the Far East.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
